row.entry:
Used to specify an alternative description to the element, that is used by the
              PDF readers.
              image {
  -oxy-alt-text: "Image about: " attr(href);
}

Used to create links in the PDF
              output.link {
  -oxy-link: attr(href);
}

Used to forward meta-information to the PDF. Represents the author of the
              publication.meta[name='author'] {
  -oxy-pdf-meta-author: attr(value);
}

Used to forward meta-information to the PDF. Represents a generic custom document
              property. Should have two strings, the name and the
              value.metadata {
  -oxy-pdf-meta-custom: attr(name) attr(value);
}

Used to forward meta-information to the PDF. Represents the description of the
              publication.
              meta[name='description'] {
  -oxy-pdf-meta-description: attr(value);
}

Used to forward meta-information to the PDF. Represents a single keyword from the
              publication. The processor should aggregate all keyword definitions and separate them
              by
              comma.keyword {
  -oxy-pdf-meta-keyword: content(text);
}

Used to forward meta-information to the PDF. Represents the keywords of the
              publication. The value should contain the keywords separated by
              commas.meta[name='keywords'] {
  -oxy-pdf-meta-keywords: attr(value);
}

Used to forward meta-information to the PDF. Represents the title of the
              publication.
              meta[name='title'] {
  -oxy-pdf-meta-title: attr(value);
}

Maps an element to a PDF accessibility tag.
              section {
  -oxy-pdf-tag-type: "Sect";
}

An oxygen extension, used to define additional styles for an element, collected
              from an attribute for example.
              div {
     font-weight:bold;
     color:red;
     -oxy-style:attr(style);
}The
              value of the style attribute from the div element, is parsed as a collection of CSS
              properties and applied over the current element styles. For instance if the style
              attribute has the value: color:green; border: 1pt solid red, it will
              combine with the existing properties,
              resulting:font-weight:bold; 
color:green;
border: 1pt solid red
